<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES -
        Cylinder Head Assembly - Connecting Under Valve Cover Harness
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="2">
        <title>Connecting Under Valve Cover Harness</title>
        <figure id="f1200499" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg2/EG2649.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="392px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Installing the Valve Cover Gasket</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Gasket With Harness</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Fuel Injector Solenoid Harness Connectors</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Glow Plug Leads</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the valve cover gasket with the UVC harness onto the cylinder head.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the electrical leads to the glow plugs by pressing the connector onto the glow
                plugs.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1200472" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd09/D0941.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Connecting the Fuel Injector Solenoid to the Wiring Harness</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Connector</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Valve Cover Gasket</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect the fuel injector electrical connector as follows:</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>On harnesses with plastic locking tabs, make sure the rubber sealing grommets are in place
                        before connecting the electrical connector to the fuel injector solenoid. Connectors with a
                        metal wire bail have no sealing grommet.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">On engines equipped with the plastic tab connectors</emph>, insert the fuel
                        injector connector into the solenoid socket. Push up on the connector until the tabs snap over
                        the indents on the solenoid.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>
                        <emph type="bold">On engines equipped with metal wire bail connectors</emph>, insert the fuel
                        injector connector into the solenoid socket. Push up and secure the connector by pulling the
                        wire clip over the indent on the solenoid.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Make sure all UVC wiring is free and clear of any moving parts and free of possible
                entrapment by the valve cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
